		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="http://home.att.ne.jp/wave/applepop/encyclopaedia/erg_m.html" class="postlink">http://home.att.ne.jp/wave/applepop/encyclopaedia/erg_m.html</a>
<br />
<br />According to the above URL, there are some Famicom games which apparently have some way of reading if there's data coming across the microphone port on the 2nd controller of the Famicom.
<br />
<br />If this is in fact true and not bullshit, does anyone know which register this is mapped to?  I've never seen it mentioned anywhere in register docs and the like, so I guess I'm having a hard time believing it...
<br />
<br />Thanks.

		

		</td>
